      <section eId="sec_CC-3515">
        <num>CC 3515</num>
        <heading>3515.  Determination of the applicable law; general and residual rule</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3515__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the relationship of each state to the parties
and the dispute; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3515__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the policies and needs of the interstate and international systems,
including the policies of upholding the justified expectations of parties and of minimizing
the adverse consequences that might follow from subjecting a party to the law of more than
one state.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110535</p>
        </authorialNote>
